Perfect! Now I can see the issue clearly. At **line 117-120**:

```typescript
// Don't open if there are already editors open
if (this.editorService.activeEditor) {
    return;
}
```

This logic prevents the welcome page from opening if there's already an active editor. According to the issue description:
- "When the folder that is being opened has files open, the chat message doesn't get passed"
- "If I open a new window the previous message is prepopulated"

The bug is that when a workspace is opened and it has files open (activeEditor exists), the welcome page doesn't open at all, so the prefill data stored in storage never gets applied because `applyPrefillData()` is never called.

